---

p
  | This tool encodes a file to Base64, which can e.g. be used to embed images in HTML, CSS or XML to&nbsp;
  a(href='/blog/site-optimization/') reduce HTTP requests
  | . Base64 encoding is designed to transport data through transport layers that are not 8-bit clean, such as mail bodies and the 7-bit&nbsp;
  abbr(title='Simple Mail Transfer Protocol') SMTP
  | &nbsp;protocol. Every 6-bit block is mapped to the characters&nbsp;
  code [a-zA-Z0-9+/]
  sup
    a(href='#footnote1') 1
  | &nbsp;and a sequence ends with&nbsp;
  code =
  | , as defined in&nbsp;
  a(href='https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3548', rel='external', target='_blank') RFC3548
  | . Base64-encoded data takes about 33% more space than the original data.
